Shape of Device, Size, and Orientation
Submergence level: Floating, Partially or Fully Submerged
Location: Shallow, Intermediate, or Deep Waters
Is it a mobile or fixed/coastal-structure-integrated (CSI) WEC?
Power-Take-Off (PTO) System: Hydraulic/pneumatic/Direct-drive/Other? ]]></description><link>key-components-and-working-principles-of-a-wec.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Key Components and working principles of a WEC.md</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 15:33:32 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[fig_classByMode]]></title><description><![CDATA[<img src="fig_classbymode.png" target="_self">]]></description><link>fig_classbymode.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">fig_classByMode.png</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 15:20:57 GMT</pubDate><enclosure url="fig_classbymode.png" length="0" type="image/png"/><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;fig_classbymode.png&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[fig_classByOrientation2]]></title><description><![CDATA[<img src="fig_classbyorientation2.png" target="_self">]]></description><link>fig_classbyorientation2.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">fig_classByOrientation2.png</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 15:20:06 GMT</pubDate><enclosure url="fig_classbyorientation2.png" length="0" type="image/png"/><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;fig_classbyorientation2.png&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[fig_classByOrientation]]></title><description><![CDATA[<img src="fig_classbyorientation.png" target="_self">]]></description><link>fig_classbyorientation.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">fig_classByOrientation.png</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 15:19:36 GMT</pubDate><enclosure url="fig_classbyorientation.png" length="0" type="image/png"/><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;fig_classbyorientation.png&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[There is an Enormous Amount of Energy in the Ocean]]></title><description><![CDATA[The estimated exploitable US wave energy is about 2,640 Terrawatt-hours per year (EPRI (2011), Mapping and Assessment of the United States Ocean Wave Energy Resource). This is nearly more than half the total annual electricity demand, which is about 4,000 TW/yr (EIA, ?year?). &lt;insert questions that motivate reading EPRI or thinking about exploitable means&gt; ]]></description><link>there-is-an-enormous-amount-of-energy-in-the-ocean.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">There is an Enormous Amount of Energy in the Ocean.md</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 15:16:32 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Some Historical Information]]></title><description><![CDATA[
The concept appeared first (formally) in 1799 by Pierre-Simon Girard in France—First Patent.
The first documented conversion of wave energy into electricity occurred in 1909 in California.
The first Oscillating Water Column (OWC) was built around 1910 by M. Bochaux-Praceique near Bordeaux in France.
The first successful attempt at using wave power to produce electricity took place in 1947 by Yoshio Masuda in Japan
The idea of wave energy as a viable commercial sector gained significant momentum in the 1970s and onwards….
